pages%2C%20and%20scanned%20them%20into%20digital%20files.%3Cp%3EVCG%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAnthropic%20bought%2C%20cut%2C%20and%20scanned%20millions%20of%20used%20books%20for%20its%20%26quot%3Bresearch%20library.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20also%20downloaded%20over%207%20million%20pirated%20books%2C%20the%20judge%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20judge%20wrote%20that%20training%20Claude%20on%20copyrighted%20books%20it%20had%20purchased%20was%20fair%20use%2C%20but%20piracy%20wasn't.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20build%20AI%20chatbot%20Claude%2C%20Anthropic%20%26quot%3Bdestructively%20scanned%26quot%3B%20millions%20of%20copyrighted%20books%2C%20wrote%20a%20judge%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERuling%20in%20a%20closely-watched%20AI%20copyright%20case%2C%20Judge%20William%20Alsup%20of%20the%20Northern%20District%20of%20California%20analyzed%20how%20Anthropic%20sourced%20data%20for%20model%20training%20purposes%2C%20including%20from%20digital%20and%20physical%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20Anthropic%20require%20vast%20amounts%20of%20input%20to%20develop%20their%20large%20language%20models%2C%20so%20they've%20tapped%20sources%20from%20social%20media%20posts%20to%20videos%20to%20books.%20Authors%2C%20artists%2C%20publishers%2C%20and%20other%20groups%20contend%20that%20the%20use%20of%20their%20work%20for%20training%20amounts%20to%20theft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlsup%20detailed%20Anthropic's%20training%20process%20with%20books%3A%20The%20OpenAI%20rival%20spent%20%26quot%3Bmany%20millions%20of%20dollars%26quot%3B%20buying%20used%20print%20books%2C%20which%20the%20company%20or%20its%20vendors%20then%20stripped%20of%20their%20bindings%2C%20cut%20the%20pages%2C%20and%20scanned%20into%20digital%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlsup%20wrote%20that%20millions%20of%20original%20books%20were%20then%20discarded%2C%20and%20the%20digital%20versions%20stored%20in%20an%20internal%20%26quot%3Bresearch%20library.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20wrote%20that%20Anthropic%2C%20which%20is%20backed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-alphabet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlphabet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20downloaded%20more%20than%207%20million%20pirated%20books%20to%20train%20Claude.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlsup%20wrote%20that%20Anthropic's%20cofounder%2C%20Ben%20Mann%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edownloaded%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%205%20million%20copies%20of%20books%20from%20Library%20Genesis%26quot%3B%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20fully%20aware%20that%20the%20material%20was%20pirated.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bdownloaded%20at%20least%202%20million%20copies%20of%20books%20from%20the%20Pirate%20Library%20Mirror%26quot%3B%20also%20knowing%20they%20were%20pirated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlsup%20wrote%20that%20Anthropic%20preferred%20to%20%26quot%3Bsteal%26quot%3B%20books%20to%20%26quot%3Bavoid%20'legal%2Fpractice%2Fbusiness%20slog%2C'%20as%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20put%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20trio%20of%20authors%20sued%20Anthropic%20in%20a%20class-action%20lawsuit%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20company%20used%20pirated%20versions%20of%20their%20books%20without%20permission%20or%20compensation%20to%20train%20its%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db8b1eb0-1e60-4069-a4f5-23d6e4891183%5C%22%3EJudge%20says%20training%20Claude%20on%20books%20was%20fair%20use%2C%20but%20piracy%20wasn't%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlsup%20ruled%20that%20Anthropic's%20use%20of%20copyrighted%20books%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models%20was%20%26quot%3Bexceedingly%20transformative%26quot%3B%20and%20qualified%20as%20fair%20use%2C%20a%20legal%20doctrine%20that%20allows%20certain%20uses%20of%20copyrighted%20works%20without%20the%20copyright%20owner's%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%20any%20reader%20aspiring%20to%20be%20a%20writer%2C%20Anthropic's%20LLMs%20trained%20upon%20works%20not%20to%20race%20ahead%20and%20replicate%20or%20supplant%20them%20%E2%80%94%20but%20to%20turn%20a%20hard%20corner%20and%20create%20something%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20decision%20to%20digitize%20millions%20of%20print%20books%20it%20had%20purchased%20fell%20under%20fair%20use%2C%20Alsup%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20Anthropic%20did%20was%20replace%20the%20print%20copies%20it%20had%20purchased%20for%20its%20central%20library%20with%20more%20convenient%20space-saving%20and%20searchable%20digital%20copies%20for%20its%20central%20library%20%E2%80%94%20without%20adding%20new%20copies%2C%20creating%20new%20works%2C%20or%20redistributing%20existing%20copies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Anthropic%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20is%20pleased%20with%20Alsup's%20ruling%20on%20using%20books%20to%20train%20LLMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20this%20approach%20is%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20with%20copyright's%20purpose%20in%20enabling%20creativity%20and%20fostering%20scientific%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Alsup%20drew%20a%20firm%20line%20when%20it%20came%20to%20piracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnthropic%20had%20no%20entitlement%20to%20use%20pirated%20copies%20for%20its%20central%20library%2C%26quot%3B%20Alsup%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BCreating%20a%20permanent%2C%20general-purpose%20library%20was%20not%20itself%20a%20fair%20use%20excusing%20Anthropic's%20piracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Alsup's%20ruling%20that%20training%20AI%20models%20on%20copyrighted%20books%20is%20fair%20use%20is%20one%20of%20the%20first%20of%20ips%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20decision%20comes%20amid%20a%20wave%20of%20lawsuits%20from%20artists%2C%20filmmakers%2C%20authors%2C%20and%20news%20outlets%20against%20major%20AI%20players%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-share-files-copyright-case-authors-guild-ilya-sutskever-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20creators%20say%20training%20AI%20models%20on%20their%20copyrighted%20work%20without%20permission%20infringes%20on%20their%20rights%2C%20AI%20execs%20argue%20they%20haven't%20violated%20copyright%20laws%20because%20the%20training%20falls%20under%20fair%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-universal-midjourney-images-evidence-copyright-infringement-lawsuit-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDisney%20sued%20AI%20image%20generator%20Midjourney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20the%20tech%20company%20ripped%20off%20famous%20characters%20in%20properties%20ranging%20from%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Simpsons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cut-pirated-millions-used-books-train-claude-copyright-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750842312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685b802685e81483682cb53c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cut-pirated-millions-used-books-train-claude-copyright-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Training%20Claude%20on%20copyrighted%20books%20it%20purchased%20was%20fair%20use%2C%20but%20piracy%20wasn't%2C%20the%20judge%20ruled.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmlee%40insider.com%20(Lee%20Chong%20Ming)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cut-pirated-millions-used-books-train-claude-copyright-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20fianc%C3%A9%20and%20I%20make%20a%20combined%20%24300%2C000%20a%20year.%20